{
  "texts": [
    "The final text representation is obtained from the [CLS] token embedding.",
    "C. Visual Feature EncodingVisual features of pre-trained CNNs (ResNet50, DenseNet169 and MobileNetV2) are obtained by eliminating top classification layers and adding global average pooling layers.",
    "These models trained on ImageNet offer stable feature representations for disaster images despite domain mismatch.",
    "Hierarchical feature extraction computes the visual feature representation:F visual = GlobalAvgPool(CNN(I)) (4)where I represents the input image and CNN denotes the convolutional feature extractor.",
    "This approach captures lowlevel patterns (textures, edges) and high-level semantic concepts (damaged buildings, flooding)."
  ]
}